Enums/FetchingStatus.html.name: FetchingStatus
Enums/FetchingStatus.html.abstract: FetchingStatus indicates current status of both resource-expensive requests (usually a combination of multiple requests) and segmented requests.

Enums/HummingKitRequestComposingError.ht.name: HummingKitRequestComposingError
Enums/HummingKitRequestComposingError.ht.abstract: Errors occur when composing API requests, might be caused by illegal amount of arguments or arguments of illegal formats.

Enums/HummingKitEnvironmentError.html.name: HummingKitEnvironmentError
Enums/HummingKitEnvironmentError.html.abstract: Errors occur when certain functionality is unsupported by the system environment, possibly due to the systemversion being outdated and not supporting some newer features.

Enums/HummingKitResponseError.html.name: HummingKitResponseError
Enums/HummingKitResponseError.html.abstract: Errors occur when the response content does not match format expected, causing parsing failure, possibly caused by corrupted response body, a new version of Apple Music API that has not been adapted by HummingKit, or errounous codes failed to be inspected beforehand.

Enums/HummingKitInternalError.html.name: HummingKitInternalError
Enums/HummingKitInternalError.html.abstract: Unexpected fatal HummingKit errors, potentially caused by internal bugs. If this type of error has occured, please file an issue on the HummingKit repo at Issues page. Thank you!
